QUESTION:

Mrs.Raja is a miser to the core.She saves money even on petite things. One dayshe heard a discount offer announced in a shop. she wants to purchase lot
of items to save her money. The discount is given only when atleast two items are bought. Since each item has different discount prices , she finds 
difficult to check the amount she has saved. So she approaches you to device a automated discount calculator to make her easy while billing. 

INPUT FORMAT:

Input consists of two floating point values denoting price of item1 and item2. 

The third input denotes the discount value in percentage. 

OUTPUT FORMAT: 

The output consists of three floating values denoting total amount, discounted price and amount saved.

 Sample Input

20.50

45.40

10

Sample Output

65.90
59.31
6.59

CODING:

#include<iostream>
#include<iomanip>
using namespace std;
int main()
{
    float a,b,c;
    float x,y,z;
    cin>>a>>b>>c;
    x=a+b;
    z=(x/100)*c;
    y=x-z;
    cout<<fixed<<setprecision(2)<<x<<endl<<fixed<<setprecision(2)<<y<<endl<<fixed<<setprecision(2)<<z;
    
}
